cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with information theory and communication aspects of interactive function computation, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.IT (Information Theory) category. The use of Gaussian sources and the study of rate-distortion regions suggest that it could also belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) category. The reconstruction constraints and the study of different functions suggest that it could belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) category. The use of multiple rounds of communication and the study of the order of communication suggest that it could belong to the cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) category. Finally, the use of jointly Gaussian sources and the study of the rate-distortion region suggest that it could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category.
